66 69H 65*4\nWheelSlUftfO 3 54*4 54h 54*4+ Hi\nStocks Mixed,\nInvestors Stay\nOn Sidelines\nNEW YORK. Aug. 2 (JP).\u2014\nCaution and light trading con\ntinued to prevail in the stock\nmarket early this afternoon.\nPrice changes'among pivotal\nissues were very narrow for the\nmost part. It was ipainly a\nmixture of small plus and\nminus signs. A few key stocks\nmoved beyond the range of a;\npoint.\nUncertainty as to the next\ndefinite trend of the market\nwas still keeping investors on\nthe sidelines, brokers said.\nVolume looked as if it would\ndip below yesterday\u2019s 1,660.000\nshares, the lowest in four';\nmonths.\nNonferrous metals were\ndampened by word from De\nfense Mobiliser Gordon Gray\nthat the Government will stop\nbuying lead and zinc for the\nstrategic stockpile. Interna\ntional Nickel dropped well over i\na point following its president\u2019s!\nprediction that both the United\nStates and Canada would soon\nstop nickel stockpiling.\nThe Associated Press average j\nof 60 stocks at noon was up 10\ncents to (184.40 With the in\ndustrials up 20 cents, the rails\ndown 10 cents and the utilities\nunchapged.\nBonds were steady In slow\ntrading.\nD. C. SECURITIES\nI.\u2014\u2014\nSALBB\nPot Elec Pwr com\u2014loo at 20*4.\nHecbt com\u2014fto at 26 V,.\nWash Oaa Lt com\u20142s at 36.\nBONDS 816 Asked\nGeorgetown Gas 1 5s 01 101 101\nPot Elec Pwr 3V,t 77.. 86\nPot Dec .\u2019wr 3s 83 82 I\nPot Dec Pwr 2\u20194s 84 72\nTer Rt&W Cp let 4s 68 08 100\nWashington Oes Ss 80 100\nPUBLIC UTILITY STOCKS\nI Amer Tel At Tel 172*v\nPot Dec Pwr 1.10 20*. 21\nPepco 2.44% pf 2.44 g4!i 51\nWnsb Gae Lt 2 38 JO I\nWash GLt cum pf 425 xB2\nj Wash OL cm cv pf 4.50 Xl2l\nI BANKS AND TRUST COMPANIES\nAmer Sec ft Tr 1.80 42 43\nBank of Bethesda t 1.50 75\ni Bank of Commerce 710 4:6\niCaplt.S *1\nLiberty 6 400\nLincoln tl 70\nNat Bav Tr 1 60 70\nRiggs new 360 130 140\nSuburban Trust 1.50 Ho 64\nI Union Trust t 1.20 3i'i 37\nj Washington 1,20 64 .16\nri\u00df* AND TITLE INSURANCE\nCol