.159 estab\nlished in the last six months\nof 1956.\nBUSINESS\nBRIEFS\nHeavy Construction Con-,\ntract awards reported in the|\nweek ended Monday mounted!\nto (401.045,000. consisting of:\n(206.232,000 in private and\n(194,813,000 in public construc\ntion, compared with (393,636,-\n000 the previous week and\n(309,454.000 for the like week\na year ago.\u2014Engineering News\nj Record.\nLoans to Brokers and dealers\non other than United States\nI Government securities held by\nmember banks in New York\nCity touted (874 million\nWednesday, a decrease of (20\nmillion from a week before,\nand a decrease of (646 million\nfrom a year before.\u2014Federal\nReserve Board.\nRail Freight Loadings for\nthe week ended July 27. was\n6,952 cars or 0.9 per cent below\nthe previous week, 86,601 cars\nor 13.3 per cent above the same\nweek last year, when a Nation\nwide steel strike was on. The\nvolume was 54.019 cars or 6.8\nper cent below the like 1955\nweek.\u2014Association of American\nRailroads.\nAmerican Barge Line and the\nCommercial Transport Corp.\n;have merged to form American\nCommercial Barge Line Co., the\nlargest Inland barge enterprise\nin the world. Its fleet will con\nsist of 51 towboats and 570\nbarges\nAluminum Limited, Canadian\naluminum producer, announced\na 1 cent a pound increase in\nthe United States price of the\ncompany's aluminum effective\nAugust 5.\nGeneral Motors reports its\nUnited States factories built\n'227.657 cars and 34.699 trucks\nand coacheff In July. This\nbrought the January-Juiy toUl\nl output to 1.770.880 cars and\n259.110 trucks. In July last\nyear GM output was 218,414\ncars and 32,067 trucks. This\nbrought the January-July total\nlast year to 1,947,776 cars and\n281,920 trucks.\nUnion Oil (Calif.) reports\nearnings for the first six months\nof 1957 of (16.727.071, or (2.17\na share, compared with (13.-\n618,151, or (1.77 a share, for the\nsame period a year ago.\nStandard Oil <lndiana! and\naffiliated companies reports net\n(earnings of 